            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jeremy Kerr",
                        "email": "jk@ozlabs.org",
                        "username": "jk-ozlabs"
                    },
                    "message": "This looks reasonable, and still complies with the spec \ud83d\ude0a\n\nThere's an opportunity to make this more resilient by recognising the framing byte at any state (say, before we enter the main 'switch' statement), and re-synchronising at that point. That means we don't discard a complete packet if the end-frame byte is dropped (ie, we don't rely on two 0x7e bytes to resync).\n\nA couple of comments inline though."
                },
                {
                    "file": "serial.c",
                    "line": 226,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jeremy Kerr",
                        "email": "jk@ozlabs.org",
                        "username": "jk-ozlabs"
                    },
                    "message": "To stay consistent with the existing code, can you use C-style comments (`/* .. */`) here, and wrap at 80?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "serial.c",
                    "line": 226,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Nikhil Namjoshi",
                        "email": "nikhilnamjoshi@google.com",
                        "username": "namjoshiniks"
                    },
                    "message": "Done"
                },
                {
